OL,6,FDigital ID cards are a "cynical ploy"
OL,7,Fdesigned to "fool" voters into
OL,8,Fthinking something is being done about
OL,9,Fimmigration, Reform UK has claimed.
OL,11,FTory leader Kemi Badenoch also
OL,12,Fdismissed the plans as a "gimmick that
OL,13,Fwill do nothing to stop the boats".
OL,15,FMeanwhile, Sir Tony Blair's think tank
OL,16,Fsaid the cards, which will be
OL,17,Fmandatory by the end of this
OL,18,FParliament, could act as a "gateway to
OL,19,Fgovernment services".
